Well, here comes my long, winding, lengthy entry, HOPEFULLY.

Well, I'll start off by saying that me and Jacob made up for a while... a few days. Then, it all spun out of control after we went to McDonalds for the "school spirit" day. It's really not called that, but for the sake of this entry being simple I shall leave it at that. So after we get home, we play for a while, I go on his computer at his house and go to homestarrunner.com with his 2 little sisters [one5 one 7]and we had some fun. One thing about Jacob's sisters is the fact that they are very loyal. By saying that, I mean ENSLAVED to Jacob. Basically, so is my brother. Whatever Jacob's opinion is, Cameron's is. First, Jacob became a "skateboarder" so low and behold, Cameron becomes one, too. Jacob refuses to wear anything but skateboarding shirts, and low and behold, Cameron is up at 6:45 in the morning yelling and crying because the outfit that my mother picked out for him intailed a shirt that didn't have a name-brand of a skateboarding company plastered onto the front. And now, the whole socks issue. Yes, something as stupid as socks. My mom got my brother a pair of very nice socks that ARE ankle socks, but not to the point where they like, sag and keep going up and down your ankle as you walk. Now he's making a big deal of it. Mer. My mom isn't going to give in and return those and get him another pair, either. *w00t!* Go mom! Anyway, Jacob's uncle and him are building this *top secret* thing called the Salsa rocket, and my brother knows about it. I don't though. Wow. That really makes me feel jealous and left out. I just *HAVE* to know what it is. So Jacob's uncle comes upstairs. He turns on loud, punk rock music. It is good, but not what I am in the mood for. Not good timing either! Just at that point, my dad and Jacob's dad start playing drums and guitar. GREAT! 2 clashing drum beats! Ew. Anyway, Jacob starts talking to his uncle about something having to do with the salsa rocket, I just KNOW it. Now I am so desperate to know what it is I am literally going to google.com to look it up! Heh. So Jacob's uncle isn't whispering anymore, at this point, and says "Jake, I only got room for 2 in the car" He says, trying not to be unfiar because he knows that I am over, too. So jacob starts whispering about some evil plan about how they could leave me behind, I just know it! 


SORRY FOR THE BREAK IN THE MIDDLE OF THE ENTRY: BUT GUESS WHAT?! I JUST CALLED JACOB AND HE TOLD ME WHAT IT WAS! Quite stupid, actually. Just a long weird skateboard. Can't beleive I wanted to know that bad. Mer. WANNA KNOW HOW I DID IT? I made an email that said the following:

Cameron has a secret crush on Emmie, Jacob's 6 year old sister! 


So....I got him out of the room and said "Cameron if you don't tell me what the Salsa Rocket is I will send this email to everyone in my adress book!" So hes like "OK ITS A SKATEBOARDING COMPANY THAT HIM AND HIS UNCLE ARE BUILDING!" So I call jacob. He spills it, because I guess that it is a skateboard.

Furthermore evidence that I should be a lawyer

*Loffloff*
Carly.


PS: HAPPY BIRTHDAY ALLI! I LOFF YEW! HAPPY belated BIRTHDAY! HEE!

Wow. I really wanted to make a long, serpentine entry, but I'm sorry. I can't, due to the fact that American Idol should be on just about now and I'm such a teeny bopper. I engage in such cliche behavior. But OH WELL.

*Yay for cliche!*

Loff,
Carly
Am going to see Mooseport in 5 minutes.

Blah.

My mom picked me up early from my dads house because this was my dad's weekend. We had a big emotion-fest and everyone was crying. W00T. My family is so dysfunctional. Where to start? My dad thinks that whenever my mom calls, it means that there will be a fight. Merr. It um, usually does, but still. My dad had to show a house today, so there was a huge contreversy over who is going to stay where when he's gone. My brother wanted to go to Jacob's [his best friend, 2 grades older than him] but at first my dad wasn't going to let him, because Jacob and I had this HHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEE fight 2 days ago, complete with fists, arms, legs and all. Here was what happened.

-Jacob ALWAYS tries to show off in front of the kids in his neighborhood, but they don't really care, because he always makes fun of me. While doing so, Jacob called me a "hippo", undenyable reffering to my weight. [also calling me names such as lezbo, retard, gayfer, etc...] He knows that pisses me off.

-I said "Jacob, if you call me that one more time I WILL hurt you, and Im not kidding."

-He responded "Oh, so if I say it one more time your saying you will hurt me?"

-I said "Yes,just one more time."

-He ran out of the room yelling "Hippo, hippo, hippo!"

-I ran down the hall, and kicked him.

-He started running downstairs, scared of me.

-We "took it outside'".

-I am taking VERBAL ABUSE while he chats away at me, calling me MANY different names that I can't quite recall.

-We fight a WHOLE LOT.

-Jacob runs inside.

-I run downstairs to tell my dad [Jacob's dad and my dad "jam out" in the basement, my dad on the drums, his dad on the electric guitar] what had happened before he got there and gave him a biased report. [he always leaves out what HE did, making me look like "the bad guy"]

-My opening line is [teary eyed, and all] "Can you please tell Jacob to stop punching me?!"

-Mr. West [Jacob's dad] is like "You punched her, boy?!!?!?!?!?!?!?!"

-We go on and on about the fight.

-Jacob is crying, blabbing on and on about how he cannot control his anger, and he can't stand me.

-We eventually go upstairs, and I stick out my hand to "truce" with him.

-He retorts "Dont you even try to apologize. Im not trying to start another fight or anything, but my answer will be no."

-We go watch "Arachnaphobia" on my couch.

-We eventually make up, and go out to dinner at Moe's.

Today's events...

-My brother calls Jacob, like he does every morning.

-He talks to him, telling him that we need to come over because my dad is going out.

-He says "Just you?" [talking to my brother]

-Cameron [my brother] says "No, Carly probably needs to come too."

-Jacob sighs.

-Cameron says "Ok, I'll call back later."

-Jacob says "Ok...Bye."

-Cameron says "Bye...."

-They hang up.

-I call back.

-Mr. West answers.

-I say "Hi, is Jacob there?"

-He says "Yes..." I hear him yelling "JJJJJJJJJJJAAAAAAAKEEEEEEE!!!!" in the background.

-Jacob answers "Hello?"

-I say "Hi..."

-He says "Hey Cameron."

-I go on and on about how this isn't Cameron.

-He says "Ok, I know. Im just kiddin'."

-I say "Ok. If Cameron comes over, I have to, too. My dad has to show a house."

-He responds "Well I guess I won't be seein' ya today, then."

-I say "Ok, bye." [He is used to me putting up a fight and going on and on about it. So I just decided to hang up.]

-He says "Byyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyeeeeeeeeee." In his silly voice, but he didn't get to finish because while he was saying it, I hang up.

So ya, that's pretty much it with the Jacob factor. Now I'm at my "soon to be stepdad's" house with a sore butt. We went to Sam's Club. Blah. 

Thats it.

Peace.

Carly
